Abstract: American and Russian military personnel monitoring data that would reflect an accidental launching of a nuclear missile as result of a Year 2000 computer glitch are relieved to be able to report that there were none; photo of Russian and American monitors sitting side by side at Y2K Strategic Stability Center at Peterson Air Force Base in Colorado Springs (M)

LeadParagraph: The new decade arrived well before dawn here today at Peterson Air Force Base, but there was more relief than celebration as the world's 24 time zones began passing from the 20th century without nuclear conflagration.
